The blinding light falls all over Cybil's body.[p]
Cybil lost her ability to see instantly, and had no idea whether her eyes were opened or closed.[p]
As Cybil's sight finally began to return to her, she felt the wind on her skin. [p]
From these two senses, she could tell that she was now outside.[p]
She doesn't sense any people...[p]
The chirping of birds...[p]
A nostalgic scent...[p]
In front of her, an area of flowerbeds spreads out.[p]
It is a scene that she has seen somewhere before.[p]
Cybil begins to walk.[p]
And then, at some point, she began to run.[p]
She passes through the trees, and once she climbed a small hill, her field of vision once again expanded.[p]
There is a cemetery.[p]
Cybil finally remembers.[p]
This is the place where her grandparents are resting.[p]
When she was young, her parents often brought her here.[p]


